0from%20Avdiivka%2C%20Donetsk%20region%20in%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EGENYA%20SAVILOV%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine's%20US-supplied%20Bradley%20fighting%20have%20become%20one%20of%20its%20most%20important%20weapons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey're%20being%20used%20for%20bold%20attacks%2C%20armored%20combat%2C%20and%20casualty%20evacuation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELimited%20numbers%20and%20new%20threats%20in%20battle%20mean%20Ukraine%20has%20to%20improvise.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20snowy%20landscape%20near%20Stepove%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine%2C%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20armored%20vehicles%20went%20head-to-head%20in%20what%20appeared%20to%20be%20a%20mismatched%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FKremlinTrolls%2Fstatus%2F1802130840912302194%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20video%20released%20by%20Ukraine's%20defense%3C%2Fa%3E%20ministry%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20Russian%20T-90%20tank%2C%20once%20billed%20by%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20as%20the%20world's%20best%2C%20faced%20off%20with%20two%20Ukrainian%2047th%20Mechanized%20Brigade%20Bradley%20armored%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bradley%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%2C%20supplied%20to%20Ukraine%20by%20the%20US%2C%20is%20primarily%20designed%20to%20carry%20infantry%20on%20assaults%20with%20the%20firepower%20to%20engage%20fortified%20positions%20and%20lighter%20armored%20vehicles%2C%20while%20leaving%20head-on%20confrontations%20with%20a%20top%20tank%20to%20the%20Abrams%20tanks%20it%20would%20normally%20fight%20alongside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bradley%20is%20equipped%20with%20capabilities%20that%20allow%20it%20to%20engage%20an%20enemy%20tank%20should%20a%20fight%20arise%2C%20but%20its%20light%20armor%20makes%20it%20vulnerable.%20The%20Russian%20T-90%20should%20have%20been%20more%20than%20a%20match%20for%20the%20Bradley%2C%20yet%20the%20American%20IFV%20came%20out%20on%20top.%20That%20battlefield%20win%20speaks%20to%20the%20strengths%20of%20the%20crew%20and%20the%20boldness%20to%20use%20the%20Bradley%20in%20tough%20battles%20without%20the%20critical%20support%20of%20more%20powerful%20main%20battle%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20video%20of%20the%20engagement%2C%20the%20Bradleys%20fire%20rounds%20repeatedly%20into%20the%20Russian%20T-90%20with%20their%2025mm%20chain-driven%20autocannon%2C%20appearing%20to%20damage%20the%20tank's%20control%20systems.%20The%20Russian%20tank's%20turret%20starts%20spinning%2C%20and%20then%20the%20tank%20veers%20off%20course%20and%20crashes%20into%20a%20tree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20example%20of%20the%20crucial%20role%20the%20Bradley%20has%20played%20for%20Ukraine%20in%20the%20front-line%20battles%20against%20Russia%2C%20where%20its%20versatility%2C%20speed%2C%20armor%2C%20and%20capable%20weapons%20have%20been%20key.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20very%20versatile%20vehicle%2C%26quot%3B%20Gustav%20Gressel%2C%20a%20military%20analyst%20at%20the%20European%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20explaining%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20Bradley%20can%20both%20transport%20and%20engage%20any%20target%20on%20the%20battlefield.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fde1e345-53d8-4e51-851a-5898f42c79e2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdapting%20after%20a%20failed%20counteroffensive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20gave%20Ukraine%20its%20first%20batch%20of%20more%20than%2060%20fighting%20vehicles%20in%20early%202023%20in%20anticipation%20of%20its%20summer%20counteroffensive%2C%20but%20their%20success%20during%20that%20endeavor%20was%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20deployed%20the%20armored%20vehicles%20in%20groups%20carrying%20troops%20in%20assault%20attacks%20on%20Russia's%20defensive%20lines%2C%20but%20Russia%20was%20able%20to%20hinder%20advances%20using%20mines%20and%20threaten%20massed%20armor%20with%20drones%2C%20artillery%2C%20and%20guided%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrone%20footage%20from%20June%20last%20year%20showed%20a%20large%20group%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F06%2F12%2Feurope%2Fukraine-offensive-battlefield-losses-progress-intl-hnk-ml%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eof%20the%20destroyed%20Bradley%20fighting%20vehicles%20near%3C%2Fa%3E%20Zaporizhzhia%20after%20they%20were%20deployed%20in%20a%20failed%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacob%20Parakilas%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20attacks%20using%20groups%20of%20vehicles%20or%20soldiers%20have%20proven%20disastrous%20because%20they%20could%20be%20more%20easily%20surveilled%20and%20attacked%20by%20drones%20%E2%80%94%20but%20Ukraine%20has%20adapted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20neither%20side%20has%20established%20air%20superiority%20in%20Ukraine%20means%20that%20such%20concentrations%20(which%20the%20Russians%20have%20attempted%20more%20often%20than%20the%20Ukrainians)%20tend%20to%20become%20disasters%2C%20with%20numerous%20vehicles%20knocked%20out%20by%20artillery%2C%20airstrikes%2C%20drones%2C%20and%20infantry%20equipped%20with%20anti-tank%20missiles%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%2C%20there%20is%20a%20much%20greater%20emphasis%20in%20Ukrainian%20usage%20on%20vehicles%20operating%20individually%20and%20flexibly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20failed%20counteroffensive%20last%20year%2C%20Ukraine%20started%20sending%20these%20vehicles%20out%20one%20or%20two%20at%20a%20time%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbradley-fighting-vehicles-prove-worth-ukraine-short-on-abrams-tanks-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20flexible%20roles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esuch%20as%20supporting%20ground%20troops%2C%20attacking%20enemy%20positions%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-used-us-bradley-ifv-evacuate-civilians-heavy-russia-fire-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeven%20evacuating%20civilians%20and%20%3C%2Fa%3Einjured%20troops%20in%20combat%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20Bradley's%20speed%20and%20armaments%2C%20other%20beneficial%20capabilities%20include%20night%20vision%2C%20which%20enables%20it%20to%20be%20deployed%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmil.in.ua%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fukrainian-3rd-assault-brigade-shows-night-battle-involving-m2-bradley-ifvs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enight-time%20combat%20missions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Ukrainian%20troops%20say%20the%20vehicle's%20armor%20provides%20greater%20survivability%20than%20some%20Soviet%20designs%20and%20is%20capable%20of%20withstanding%20some%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edirect%20Russian%20hits%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F09%2F05%2Feurope%2Fukraine-zaporizhzhia-robotyne-bradley-intl-cmd%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%20reported%20last%20September.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGressel%2C%20the%20European%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%20analyst%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20threat%20posed%20by%20drones%20close%20to%20Russian%20front%20lines%20has%20led%20to%20Bradleys%20operating%20alone%20in%20rapid%20action%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20armored%20vehicles%20dash%20in%2C%20fulfill%20their%20combat%20mission%2C%20and%20then%20withdraw%20as%20fast%20as%20they%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gressel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20have%20been%20other%20combat%20adaptations.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAnalysts%20and%20troops%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnational-security%2F2024%2F06%2F12%2Fukraine-bradley-fighting-vehicles-combat-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%20that%20artillery%20shortages%20caused%20by%20the%20earlier%20US%20Congress%20aid%20block%20meant%20the%20vehicles%20were%20even%20being%20used%20to%20target%20buildings%20that%20would%20normally%20only%20be%20attacked%20from%20long%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bradley%20has%20a%20proven%20record%20as%20a%20versatile%20weapon.%20Its%20American%20crews%20destroyed%20many%20Iraqi%20tanks%20and%20armored%20vehicles%20with%20its%2025mm%20cannon%20and%20TOW%20missiles%20during%20the%201991%20Gulf%20War%2C%20and%20it%20later%20played%20key%20roles%20in%20the%20armored%20thrust%20into%20Baghdad%20in%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20also%20finding%20these%20capable%20weapons%20useful.%20In%20May%2C%20a%20Bradley%20immobilized%20a%20Russian%20MT-LB%20tracked%20armored%20vehicle%20in%20a%20clash%20near%20Adviikva%2C%20the%20scene%20of%20some%20of%20the%20war's%20fiercest%20fighting.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FRALee85%2Fstatus%2F1797310206021423387%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOnly%20weeks%20later%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ea%20Bradley%20took%20out%20two%20BTR-82%20Russian%20armored%20troop%20carriers%20in%20the%20same%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20drone%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66165d5416bde8d4ead73cd3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20military%20drone%20is%20loaded%20with%20dummy%20grenades%20for%20target%20practice%20in%20April%202023.%3Cp%3EScott%20Peterson%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20even%20adapted%20to%20modern%20threats%20in%20some%20cases.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20instance%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FDefenceU%2Fstatus%2F1805908109950386292%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evideo%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20by%20Ukraine's%20defense%20ministry%20in%20June%20shows%20a%20Bradley%20even%20taking%20out%20a%20Russian%20drone%20using%20its%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eguns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20head-to-head%20battles%20with%20Russian%20tanks%2C%20the%20Bradley%20lacks%20the%20combat%20power%20of%20the%20heavily-armed%2C%20heavily-armored%20tanks%2C%20but%20its%20chain%20gun%20has%20a%20rapid%20rate%20of%20fire%20that%20can%20prove%20effective.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGressel%20said%20that%20even%20if%20the%20Bradley%20%26quot%3Bcan't%20penetrate%20a%20%5BRussian%20tank%5D%20with%20the%20autocannon%2C%20the%20autocannon%20immobilises%20the%20Russian%20tanks%2C%20and%20usually%20damages%20either%20their%20cannons%20and%2For%20optics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d1c9a99-68db-4be7-8b70-922d81ea1a01%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELearning%20lessons%20from%20the%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20drawing%20lessons%20from%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20way%20it%20is%20using%20the%20Bradleys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParakilas%2C%20the%20RAND%20analyst%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20is%20modifying%20the%20Bradley%20vehicles%20to%20better%20defend%20them%20against%20the%20drone%20and%20air%20attacks%20that%20proved%20devastating%20against%20the%20western-supplied%20armored%20vehicles%20in%20summer%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20integrating%20weapons%20that%20can%20%26quot%3Bintercept%20incoming%20threats%20before%20they%20can%20strike%20the%20vehicle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20received%20300%20Bradleys%2C%20of%20which%20they've%20lost%20at%20least%2090%2C%20according%20to%20open-source%20trackers.%20The%20vehicles%2C%20which%20came%20in%20roughly%2010%20times%20the%20numbers%20as%20Abrams%20tanks%2C%20have%20proven%20tremendously%20valuable%20to%20Ukraine%20on%20the%20front%20line%20as%20all-purpose%20vehicles%2C%20even%20with%20the%20threats%20they%20face.%20And%20a%20big%20part%20of%20that%20goes%20back%20to%20usage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20pretty%20clear%20that%20the%20Ukrainians%20are%20using%20Bradleys%20as%20jacks%20of%20all%20trades%20and%2C%20given%20their%20high%20value%20and%20limited%20numbers%2C%20keeping%20them%20separate%20to%20prevent%20a%20single%20attack%20from%20destroying%20more%20than%20one%20at%20a%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Parakilas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-bradley-fighting-vehicles-unorthodox-ways-russia-war-putin-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721985302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667bf7a7d1c84a0eaca7e2be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-bradley-fighting-vehicles-unorthodox-ways-russia-war-putin-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ukraine%20is%20using%20the%20US-supplied%20Bradley%20fighting%20vehicles%20in%20unorthodox%20ways%20and%20making%20an%20impact.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tporter%40businessinsider.com%20(Tom%20Porter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-bradley-fighting-vehicles-unorthodox-ways-russia-war-putin-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Barack%20and%20Michelle%20Obama%20Endorse%20Kamala%20Harris%20for%20President%3A%20%E2%80%98She%20Has%20Our%20Full%20Support%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721984939000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fobama-harris.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236086147%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Barack%20and%20Michelle%20Obama%20have%20officially%20endorsed%20Kamala%20Harris%20for%20U.S.%20president.%20The%20Obamas%20shared%20the%20news%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%20on%20Friday%2C%20writing%3A%20%E2%80%9CEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20Michelle%20and%20I%20called%20our%20friend%20%40KamalaHarris.%20We%20told%20her%20we%20think%20she%E2%80%99ll%20make%20a%20fantastic%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20that%20she%20has%20our%20full%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2