ing%20skyscrapers%2C%20candy-colored%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsee-inside-public-housing-singapore-hdb-million-dollars-blue-zone-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20housing%20apartment%20blocks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20lush%20green%20spaces%20%E2%80%94%20Singapore%20has%20long%20been%20recognized%20for%20its%20meticulous%20urban%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city-state%20is%20home%20to%20a%20population%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.population.gov.sg%2Four-population%2Fpopulation-trends%2Foverview%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E5.9%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20despite%20spanning%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.singstat.gov.sg%2Fpublications%2Freference%2Febook%2Fsociety%2Fenvironment%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520main%2520island%2520of%2520Singapore%2CWater%2520Mark%2520cadastral%2520survey%2520boundaries.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E284%20square%20miles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20much%20of%20the%20credit%20for%20the%20city's%20layout%20goes%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmorrow.sg%2Fdr-liu-thai-ker%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiu%20Thai%20Ker%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2086%2C%20an%20urban%20planner%20who's%20often%20considered%20the%20architect%20of%20modern%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20older%20Asian%20man%20with%20white%20hair%20and%20a%20suit%20smiling%20for%20the%20camera.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669de42bfb2b6bedb05914e0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELiu%20Thai%20Ker%20is%20often%20lauded%20as%20the%20architect%20of%20modern%20Singapore.%3Cp%3EProvided%20by%20Morrow%20Architects%20and%20Planners%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20time%20at%20the%20Housing%20Development%20Board%2C%20or%20HDB%2C%20Liu%20oversaw%20the%20building%20of%2020%20new%20towns%20and%20over%20half%20a%20million%20housing%20units%20in%20the%20city.%20In%20the%20late%2080s%20and%20early%2090s%2C%20he%20also%20served%20as%20the%20chief%20planner%20of%20the%20Urban%20Redevelopment%20Authority%2C%20where%20he%20developed%20Singapore's%20land-use%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F05%2F24%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Fsingapore-public-housing-urban-planner.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiu%20has%20said%20he%20has%20two%20regrets%20about%20how%20Singapore%20was%20planned%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228410c561-8267-4462-80d5-ddaa3060ded9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreating%20bicycle%20paths%20for%20the%20city%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20in%20the%20HDB%2C%20I%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20planning%20bicycle%20paths%20for%20citizens%2C%26quot%3B%20Liu%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAt%20that%20time%2C%20my%20colleagues%20and%20I%20had%20several%20discussions%2C%20but%20eventually%20decided%20against%20it%20due%20to%20Singapore's%20tropical%20climate%2C%20which%20we%20felt%20would%20be%20too%20hot%20for%20cycling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20lone%20cyclist%20riding%20his%20bike%20along%20a%20path%20at%20the%20Gardens%20by%20The%20Bay%20in%20Singapore.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669a07fafb2b6bedb0589aa1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Singapore%20government%20is%20planning%20to%20double%20the%20city's%20existing%20cycling%20network%20by%202030.%3Cp%3EAscentXmedia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20attitudes%20of%20Singaporeans%20and%20people%20around%20the%20world%20today%20have%20changed%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiu%20says%20he%20wishes%20he%20had%20developed%20bike%20sections%20for%20roads%20and%20incorporated%20bicycle%20paths%20into%20streets.%20%26quot%3BFortunately%2C%20I%20believe%20it%20is%20still%20possible%20to%20do%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20local%20outlet%20The%20Straits%20Times%20reported%20that%20local%20authorities%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.straitstimes.com%2Fsingapore%2Ftransport%2Fnew-cycling-paths-in-7-towns-will-be-progressively-completed-from-2024-lta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplanning%20to%20double%20the%20city's%20existing%20cycling%20network%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20530km%20now%20to%201%2C300km%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntegrating%20more%20bicycle%20paths%20would%20enhance%20Singapore's%20sustainability%20efforts%2C%20aligning%20with%20global%20trends%20in%20urban%20development%20seen%20in%20cities%20like%20Copenhagen%20and%20Amsterdam%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasd.sutd.edu.sg%2Fpeople%2Ffaculty%2Fthomas-schroepfer%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThomas%20Schroepfer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20architecture%20and%20sustainability%20design%20at%20the%20Singapore%20University%20of%20Technology%20and%20Design%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224832%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sign%20describing%20shared%20tracks%20for%20pedestrians%20and%20cyclists%20in%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669a115449138fa6f6e3bcd9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223624%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShared%20tracks%20%E2%80%94%20for%20pedestrians%20and%20cyclists%20%E2%80%94%20are%20commonly%20found%20in%20parks%20and%20other%20recreational%20areas%20in%20Singapore.%3Cp%3Eagfit%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCreating%20bicycle%20paths%20is%20crucial%20for%20sustainable%20cities%20and%20would%20benefit%20Singapore%20by%20reducing%20traffic%20congestion%2C%20lowering%20emissions%2C%20and%20improving%20public%20health%20through%20increased%20physical%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20Schroepfer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20bicycle%20paths%20can%20boost%20local%20economies%2C%20as%20cyclists%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20stop%20at%20local%20businesses%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22074f9e83-7b88-45b6-af47-9ca34ce5b0a4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPreserving%20squatter%20huts%20for%20the%20younger%20generations%20to%20see%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESingapore's%20skyline%20today%20includes%20some%20world-famous%20builds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-toured-singapores-marina-bay-sands-resort-rooftop-pool-tour-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMarina%20Bay%20Sands%20and%20its%20infinity%20pool%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There's%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foasia-hotel-downtown-singapore-green-living-tower-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOasia%20Hotel%20in%20downtown%20Singapore%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20been%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bliving%20tower%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20greenery%20that's%20intentionally%20overgrowing%20its%20620-foot%20facade.%20And%20there's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visitsingapore.com%2Fneighbourhood%2Ffeatured-neighbourhood%2Fmarina-bay%2Fesplanades-theatres-on-the-bay%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEsplanade%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20theater%20by%20the%20Singapore%20River%20that's%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BThe%20Durian%26quot%3B%20for%20its%20resemblance%20to%20the%20tropical%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%2060s%2C%20Singapore%20looked%20drastically%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mnd.gov.sg%2Four-city-our-home%2Four-early-struggles%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMinistry%20of%20National%20Development%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20estimated%20300%2C000%20people%20lived%20in%20semi-permanent%20shelters%20in%20squatter%20areas%2C%20while%20another%20250%2C000%20were%20in%20rented%20partitioned%20cubicles%20in%20old%20shophouses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223508%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black%20and%20white%20photo%20of%20a%20bustling%20street%20in%20Singapore%20in%201962.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669a0d9e49138fa6f6e3bcc3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222728%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhile%20there%20are%20no%20longer%20any%20squatter%20settlements%20in%20Singapore%2C%20other%20architectural%20features%2C%20such%20as%20shophouses%2C%20have%20been%20conserved.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Pratt%2FKeystone%20Features%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20HDB%2C%20the%20government%20managed%20to%20rehouse%20around%201.2%20million%20squatters%20by%201985%2C%20Liu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20it%20is%20a%20very%20gratifying%20achievement%2C%20my%20regret%20is%20that%20we%20did%20not%20attempt%20to%20save%20a%20few%20hectares%20of%20the%20original%20squatter%20colonies%20for%20Singaporeans%20of%20today%2C%20and%20future%20generations%20to%20see%20how%20far%20we%20have%20transformed%20the%20city%20to%20its%20present%20condition%2C%26quot%3B%20Liu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20amount%20of%20photographs%20or%20written%20text%2C%20can%20convey%20adequately%20the%20poor%20living%20conditions%20of%20our%20squatters%20in%20the%20early%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BAs%20we%20always%20say%2C%20seeing%20is%20believing.%20While%20regretfully%2C%20we%20can%20no%20longer%20see%20our%20squatter%20colonies%20today%2C%20this%20also%20implies%20that%20Singaporeans%20are%20living%20in%20much%20better%20conditions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221811%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Several%20high-rise%20public%20apartment%20blocks%20in%20Singapore.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669a1d4e80d4d5da13d544ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221358%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMost%20of%20Singapore's%20population%20lives%20in%20high-rise%20public%20housing%20apartment%20blocks.%3Cp%3Efiftymm99%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcapti