China's%20version%20of%20X%2C%20in%20similar%20threads%2C%20which%20were%20later%20censored.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20experts%20and%20think%20tanks%20have%20long%20said%20this%20is%20a%20policy%20change%20that%20an%20aging%20China%20desperately%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9f85057-4406-46ab-bf84-cb4c35c75535%5C%22%3EChina's%20low%20retirement%20age%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20with%20blue-collar%20jobs%20in%20China%20can%20retire%20and%20collect%20pension%20checks%20as%20early%20as%2050%2C%20and%20those%20in%20offices%20can%20leave%20the%20workforce%20at%2055.%20Even%20the%20retirement%20age%20of%2060%20for%20Chinese%20men%20is%20below%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd-ilibrary.org%2Fsites%2Fca401ebd-en%2F1%2F3%2F3%2F6%2Findex.html%3FitemId%3D%2Fcontent%2Fpublication%2Fca401ebd-en%26_csp_%3D9d37797bd84847326841f27f588be463%26itemIGO%3Doecd%26itemContentType%3Dbook%23%3A~%3Atext%3Dlinklink%2520copied!-%2CNormal%2520retirement%2520age%2Cyears%2520(hence%2520around%25202064).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20average%20of%20about%2064.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20the%20standard%20set%20in%201951%2C%20but%20it's%20outdated%20because%20if%20we%20look%20back%2C%20the%20life%20expectancy%20at%20birth%20was%2043%20in%201950%20and%20then%2048%20in%201958%2C%26quot%3B%20Sabrina%20Luk%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20social%20sciences%20at%20the%20Nanyang%20Technological%20University%20in%20Singapore%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20life%20expectancy%20has%20now%20soared%20to%2075.4%20years%20for%20men%20and%2080.8%20years%20for%20women%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stats.gov.cn%2Fsj%2Fndsj%2F2023%2Findexeh.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficial%20government%20statistics.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20change%20was%20probably%2020%20years%20overdue%2C%26quot%3B%20Shaun%20Rein%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Shanghai-based%20China%20Market%20Research%20Group%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20ridiculous%20that%20people%20would%20graduate%20from%20college%20or%20from%20a%20vocational%20school%20at%20age%2022%2C%20work%20for%2028%20years%2C%20and%20then%20be%20retired%20for%20another%2030%20to%2040%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuk%2C%20who%20researches%20aging%20in%20Asia%2C%20said%20Beijing%20could%20look%20at%20creating%20a%20national%20standard%20in%20retirement%20ages%20across%20genders.%20It's%20currently%20running%20a%20lopsided%20policy%20of%20letting%20women%20retire%20up%20to%2010%20years%20earlier%20despite%20them%20living%20significantly%20longer%20on%20average%20than%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20almost%20every%20country%2C%20women%20outlive%20men%20by%20about%20four%20years%20on%20average%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20China%2C%20the%20women%20live%20more%20than%20five%20years%20longer%20than%20men.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20think%20tanks%2C%20including%20the%20state-run%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fcisscass.com%2Ffazhanbginfo.aspx%3Fids%3D23%26fl%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20Academy%20of%20Social%20Sciences%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20forecast%20that%20the%20country%20will%20aim%20for%20all%20workers%20to%20retire%20at%2065.%20There%20is%20no%20official%20word%20yet%20on%20the%20new%20retirement%20ages%20or%20whether%20they%20will%20be%20standardized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b4bdc3a4-30a8-441e-be43-cac3fd1263a0%5C%22%3EThe%20pension%20problem%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKey%20to%20the%20retirement%20overhaul%20are%20China's%20pension%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20Chinese%20workers%20receive%20a%20state%20pension%2C%20which%20can%20be%20boosted%20by%20retirement%20funds%20from%20employers%20and%20personal%20contributions.%20The%20state%20fund%20is%20by%20far%20the%20most%20relied%20upon%20by%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20country%2C%20like%20the%20rest%20of%20East%20Asia%2C%20is%20aging%20rapidly.%20An%20estimated%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fchina%2Fhealth-topics%2Fageing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E254%20million%20of%20its%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0are%20over%2060%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-aging-superaged-society-demographic-crisis-catch-up-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20that%20number%20is%20expected%20to%20grow%20by%202040%20to%20400%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20more%20than%20the%20entire%20US%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20big%20problem%20for%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20Gu%20Qingyang%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20public%20policy%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThe%20state%20fund%20depends%20on%20government%20budgets%2C%20and%20this%20is%20highly%20dependent%20on%20the%20whole%20economy.%20And%20we%20all%20know%20China's%20current%20economic%20performance%20is%20not%20that%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20retirees%20to%20support%20and%20a%20dwindling%20young%20workforce%20to%20feed%20the%20funds%2C%20China%20fears%20it%20will%20run%20out%20of%20money%20to%20give%20out.%20CASS%20estimated%20in%202019%20that%20pension%20reserves%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fcisscass.com%2Fyanjiucginfo.aspx%3Fids%3D26%26fl%3D3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emay%20drain%20completely%20by%202035.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20was%20before%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshanghai-lockdown-surreal-photos-ghost-town-amid-covid-lockdown-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ezero-COVID%20mandate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20local%20governments%20%E2%80%94%20who%20are%20typically%20responsible%20for%20funding%20state%20pensions%20%E2%80%94%20spent%20years%20pouring%20billions%20into%20lockdowns%2C%20quarantine%20centers%2C%20testing%20facilities%2C%20and%20swab%20kits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20China%20emerged%20from%20its